# Expo public variables for app/mobile
# Copy to .env (or .env.local) and fill values.
#
# --- EAS Build (Expo dashboard) ---
# eas.json maps each profile to an EAS environment — variables must exist for THAT environment:
#   development + development-simulator → "development"
#   preview → "preview"
#   production → "production"
# Create the SAME keys in each environment you build (or duplicate the variable across envs in the UI).
# Client bundle / app.config embedding: EXPO_PUBLIC_* must be visibility "Plain text" or "Sensitive"
# (NOT "Secret" — secrets are not passed into the JS bundle).
#
# --- TestFlight / App Store (EAS production) ---
# In Expo → Project → Environment variables, set (no trailing slash on API):
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.snaproad.app
#   API_URL=https://api.snaproad.app
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN, EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY,
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY
# Then: cd app/mobile && npm run eas:build:prod:ios
# Railway API must return GET /health with "checks.database":"ok" (fix Supabase keys + migrations if degraded).
#
# To push local app/backend/.env + app/frontend/.env + app/mobile/.env into Expo (EAS) Production:
#   From repo root: npm run eas:sync-env   (requires `npx eas-cli login`; does not print secret values).

# API base (no trailing slash). Default app behavior uses production:
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://api.snaproad.app
API_URL=https://api.snaproad.app
# Local backend instead (optional): same Wi‑Fi use http://YOUR_MAC_LAN_IP:8001, or tunnel:
# 1) Start backend: from repo root, `npm run dev:backend` (listens on :8001).
# 2) `cd app/mobile && npm run tunnel:api` → paste the https://....trycloudflare.com URL here.
# 3) Restart Metro.
#
# If the dev client shows "Could not connect to development server", Expo needs the Metro URL explicitly.
# Prefer: `npm run start:dev:lan` from app/mobile (sets EXPO_PACKAGER_PROXY_URL automatically), or from repo root `npm run dev:mobile:lan`.
# Manual fix (shell, before expo start): export EXPO_PACKAGER_PROXY_URL=http://YOUR_MAC_LAN_IP:8081
#   and export REACT_NATIVE_PACKAGER_HOSTNAME=YOUR_MAC_LAN_IP
#
# If Expo shows "could not connect to development server" / "Tunnel connection has been closed" (ngrok):
#   From repo root: `npm run dev:mobile:lan` (backend + Expo --lan). Phone and Mac must be on the same Wi‑Fi.
#   Or keep --tunnel and set a free ngrok authtoken: https://dashboard.ngrok.com → `export NGROK_AUTH_TOKEN=...`
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL is set above (production). Comment it out and uncomment one line below for local API only:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.XXX:8001
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://YOUR-trycloudflare-URL.trycloudflare.com
# Let admin/partner profiles use the driver app (local Metro, dev client, or EAS preview — not store production).
# Preview builds use NODE_ENV=production; the app still allows staff when EAS_BUILD_PROFILE is preview/development.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_ALLOW_STAFF_IN_DRIVER_APP=true
# Mapbox public access token (pk.). Scoped in Mapbox to SnapRoad apps; safe to ship in clients.
# Committed here so `cp .env.example .env` gets a working map for local/dev client. Rotate in Mapbox if needed.
# EAS / TestFlight: also set EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN in Expo → Environment variables for each profile.
#
# Quick local / internal preview:
#   1) Copy this file to .env and set EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN — `expo start` / dev client read it from the bundle.
#   2) EAS: set EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN in the same Expo "environment" as your build profile (Plain text / Sensitive).
#   3) Production profile: empty token fails the build unless ALLOW_MISSING_MAPBOX_TOKEN=1 (no map).
# Optional: EXPO_PUBLIC_DEBUG_MAPBOX=1 logs Mapbox resolution (prefix only) in release builds for one-off debugging.
EXPO_PUBLIC_MAPBOX_TOKEN=your-mapbox-public-token
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# Google OAuth (Supabase): EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_* must be the SAME project as Auth → Providers → Google.
# Add redirect URL in Supabase → Authentication → URL Configuration: snaproad://auth
# Google Cloud → OAuth Web client → Authorized redirect URIs must include:
#   https://<project-ref>.supabase.co/auth/v1/callback
# If the anon key does not match the project (wrong env / old key / typo), you may see "Invalid API key" after Google.
# Rebuild the app after changing EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY.
# If Google OAuth opens Safari to "env-not-configured.supabase.co", the production build is missing BOTH
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY in EAS — placeholders are baked in at build time.
EXPO_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# Sentry (optional): same DSN works for @sentry/react-native; use "Sensitive" or "Plain text" in Expo (not Secret) so it can ship in the client.
# Logs: enableLogs + consoleLoggingIntegration are enabled in App.tsx when DSN is set. In Sentry → Logs, confirm your org has the Logs product.
# One-off verify after changing .env: EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_LOG_TEST=1 then reload once; look for log_source=sentry_test in Sentry.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_DSN=
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SENTRY_LOG_TEST=1

# --- EAS Submit → TestFlight (non-interactive) ---
# 1) App Store Connect → your app → General → App Information → copy the numeric "Apple ID".
# 2) One-time: cd app/mobile && npx eas-cli credentials -p ios → set up App Store Connect API key for EAS Submit.
# 3) From app/mobile:
#      export ASC_APP_ID=1234567890
#      npm run eas:submit:ios
# Optional: EXPO_APPLE_APP_SPECIFIC_PASSWORD (+ appleId in eas.json submit.production.ios) if not using an API key.
#
# --- EAS development build (Mapbox / native modules need a dev client, not Expo Go) ---
# From app/mobile: npx eas-cli login && npm run eas:build:dev:ios   (or :android)
# Install the build on device, then: npm run start:dev or start:dev:tunnel and open the app.

# Optional legacy aliases (app.config reads some non-Mapbox keys only)
# API_URL=
# SUPABASE_URL=
# SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=
# STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=

# --- Navigation ETA + traffic refresh (EXPO_PUBLIC_* baked in at build / Metro bundle time) ---
# Restart Metro (or rebuild EAS) after changing these. Defaults in code = off if unset.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_NAV_REFRESH_V2=1   # policy-driven refresh + caps (replaces fixed ~3 min loop)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_NAV_EDGE_ETA=1     # per-edge duration when Map annotations align (else proportional split)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_NAV_ETA_BLEND=1    # short-horizon blend of model ETA with GPS speed vs remaining distance
# EXPO_PUBLIC_NAV_SERVER_ETA=1    # optional: client calls /api/navigation/canonical-eta when wired as authority

# --- Mapbox Navigation SDK (native turn-by-turn) ---
# Secret token (sk.) for downloading Navigation SDK during native builds.
# Create at mapbox.com -> Account -> Tokens with Downloads:Read scope.
# iOS: also add to ~/.netrc (machine api.mapbox.com login mapbox password <token>)
# EAS: set as a secret in Expo dashboard for each build environment.
# MAPBOX_DOWNLOADS_TOKEN=

# Native nav: when 1, "Start Navigation" launches the native Mapbox Navigation UI.
# Default off — legacy RN custom nav is used. Enable for beta testing.
# EXPO_PUBLIC_NAV_NATIVE_SDK=1
